    <section id="roadmap">
      <h2 class="section-title">Networking Career Roadmap</h2>
      <p class="intro-text">
        Follow this step-by-step path to build your networking knowledge from beginner to advanced levels.
        Each stage builds on the previous one, providing a structured learning journey.
      </p>
      
      <div class="roadmap">
        <div class="roadmap-step">
          <h3>1. Network Fundamentals</h3>
          <p>Start with the basic concepts that form the foundation of networking:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>OSI and TCP/IP models</li>
            <li>IP addressing and subnetting</li>
            <li>Network types and topologies</li>
            <li>Basic network hardware (routers, switches, cables)</li>
            <li>Recommended certification: CompTIA Network+</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="roadmap-step">
          <h3>2. Network Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Learn about the physical and logical components of networks:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Switching concepts (VLANs, trunking, STP)</li>
            <li>Routing basics (static vs dynamic)</li>
            <li>Wireless networking fundamentals</li>
            <li>Network cabling and connections</li>
            <li>Hands-on practice: Set up a small home network</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="roadmap-step">
          <h3>3. Routing & Switching</h3>
          <p>Dive deeper into how data moves through networks:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Routing protocols (OSPF, EIGRP, BGP)</li>
            <li>Advanced switching (VTP, DTP, port security)</li>
            <li>Network segmentation strategies</li>
            <li>Troubleshooting connectivity issues</li>
            <li>Recommended certification: CCNA</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="roadmap-step">
          <h3>4. Network Security</h3>
          <p>Learn to protect networks from threats:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Firewall implementation and configuration</li>
            <li>VPN technologies</li>
            <li>Security protocols and encryption</li>
            <li>Intrusion detection and prevention</li>
            <li>Security best practices and policies</li>
            <li>Recommended certification: Security+</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="roadmap-step">
          <h3>5. Cloud Networking</h3>
          <p>Explore how networking works in cloud environments:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Virtual networks in AWS, Azure, GCP</li>
            <li>Software-defined networking (SDN)</li>
            <li>Hybrid cloud connectivity</li>
            <li>Cloud security and compliance</li>
            <li>Recommended certification: AWS Solutions Architect or Azure Administrator</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="roadmap-step">
          <h3>6. Advanced Topics</h3>
          <p>Specialize in cutting-edge networking technologies:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Network automation and programmability</li>
            <li>Container networking (Docker, Kubernetes)</li>
            <li>IPv6 implementation</li>
            <li>5G and edge computing</li>
            <li>Network design and optimization</li>
            <li>Recommended certification: CCNP or specialized certifications</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  
